At the hearing, the fiscal court shall consider testimony offered at the hearing and any other relevant information including, but not limited to, the following:
Present and projected need for the service by the sanitation district;
Population density of the sanitation district;
Existence of alternate providers of services;
Revenue base of the sanitation district, including but not limited to, assessed valuation, bonding capacity, and user fees; and
Consequences of alteration of the sanitation district's boundaries on the effectiveness and efficiency of the sanitation district.
